Comments :
In September 1971, a platoon of recruits arrives in Ft. Polk, LA, for 
infantry training before leaving for war. The final week takes place in 
Tigerland, a swamp similar to Vietnam. Jim Paxton has enlisted; he wants 
to experience everything and write books later. He befriends Roland Bozz, 
a cool Texan with a gift for getting into trouble and for helping misfits 
get discharges. At least one sociopath in the platoon hates Bozz, even as 
the sergeants grudgingly recognize his leadership abilities. As the platoon 
heads into its week in Tigerland, Paxton&#039;s body gives out, Bozz makes plans 
to go AWOL, and the sociopath gets hold of live ammo. Is the Louisiana swamp 
more dangerous than the DMZ ?
